---
// Credits section for the landing page.
---

<div class="credits-section">
  <h2>Credits</h2>
  <p>vcfkit exists because of decades of work by others.</p>

  <div class="credits-grid">
    <div class="credit-block">
      <div class="credit-name">htslib and bcftools</div>
      <p class="credit-body">
        The reference implementations for VCF/BCF processing. Created and maintained by the
        <a href="https://www.sanger.ac.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Wellcome Sanger Institute</a>.
        Primary authorship: Heng Li (original author), Petr Danecek (bcftools lead), and hundreds of
        contributors over 15+ years. vcfkit's normalization was developed by reading bcftools source.
        Differential tests validate against bcftools output — if they diverge, vcfkit is wrong by default.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="credit-block">
      <div class="credit-name">noodles</div>
      <p class="credit-body">
        Pure-Rust I/O for VCF, BCF, FASTA, and chain files, by
        <a href="https://github.com/zaeleus" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Michael Macias</a>.
        Without noodles this project wouldn't exist in its current form.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="credit-block">
      <div class="credit-name">Tan, Abecasis, Kang 2015</div>
      <p class="credit-body">
        "Unified representation of genetic variants," <em>Bioinformatics</em> 31(13):2202–2204.
        <a href="https://doi.org/10.1093/bioinformatics/btv112" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          DOI: 10.1093/bioinformatics/btv112
        </a>.
        The normalization algorithm implemented in <code>vcfkit normalize</code>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="credit-block">
      <div class="credit-name">UCSC Genome Browser</div>
      <p class="credit-body">
        Chain files and reference FASTAs used by <code>vcfkit liftover</code>.
        Download chain files from
        <a href="https://hgdownload.soe.ucsc.edu/goldenPath/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          UCSC's FTP archive
        </a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
